Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
init_layout_view(25.10)                                init_layout_view(25.10)

Name
       init_layout_view

Syntax
         init_layout_view<list_of_views>

       Type: String

       Default: NULL

       Specifies  the  list  of OpenAccess view names to be processed for cell
       layout viewing (GDSII equivalent). This global  variable  replaces  the
       previous rda_Input(ui_oa_layoutname) configuration file variable.

       The  init_layout_view  global  is also used in the case where a Verilog
       netlist is read and views from the init_layout_view list  are  used  in
       the  Quick  Abstract Inference flow to derive abstract information from
       layout views for cells that were not processed from  the  libraries  in
       the init_oa_ref_lib list. It is used by the init_design command.

Example
              * The  following command specifies LAY3 as the layout view to be
                imported.

                set init_layout_view {LAY3}

Related Information
              * init_design

              * init_oa_ref_lib

